---
title: Spiced Lentils with Grilled Halloumi and Red Onion Textures
description: Great food is all about dimensions. For some people, food has only one dimension: they eat it for fuel. For others it has two dimensions: it not only keeps them going, but it tastes good too. However, as with Oscar winning blockbusters about blue people from Pandora, the full experience can really only be enjoyed in 3D. For this dish, we’ve added texture in the form of crispy onions and the hearty mouth filling indulgence that is grilled halloumi. Blue and red disposable glasses optional.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/spiced-lentils-with-grilled-halloumi-efb469c4.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/spiced-lentils-with-grilled-hall-b6e93cc7.pdf
cuisine: Fusion
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/spiced-lentils-with-grilled-hall-5757ee24f8b25ee2578b4568
servings: 2
time required: 35 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 780 kcal
  fat: 35 g
  saturated fat: 17 g
  carbohydrates: 74 g
  sugar: 10 g
  protein: 45 g
---

Chop the @cherry tomatoes{1/2}(chopped into quarters). Drain and rinse the @green lentils{1%small pot}. Peel and chop the @red onion{1}(peeled and sliced thinly) in half lengthways then slice thinly. Slice the @halloumi{1}(sliced into ½cm slices) and chop the @pistachios{some}(chopped).

Mix the @plain flour{1%cup} with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch} in a #bowl{}. Mix your onion slices in the flour to thoroughly coat them.

Heat a splash of @oil{splash} in a #non-stick pan{} on medium-high heat. When the oil is hot, fry off your onion in small batches. Tip: By not overcrowding the pan you can brown off the onion rather than stew it. When your onion is really crispy, remove to the side (on #kitchen paper{} preferably).

In the (now empty) pan, heat another splash of oil on medium heat. Add the @ras-el-hanout{some} and cook for ~{1%minute} (with a pinch of @?sugar{pinch} if you have some). Mix in a third of your tomatoes and season with a pinch of salt and a few grinds of pepper.

Add the @basmati rice{1/2%cup} to the pan and stir for ~{1%minute}. Pour in the @boiling water{175%ml} and turn the heat to its lowest setting. Cover the pan with a #lid{} and leave for ~{10%minutes}. Remove the pan from the heat for ~{10%minutes} (don't remove the lid).

Pre-heat your #grill{} to high. While your grill heats up, brush your halloumi slices very lightly with oil. Lay the slices on a #baking tray{} and grill as close to the heat as possible. Cook until thoroughly browned off on both sides.

Finely chop the @baby spinach{1/2%bag}(finely chopped). Once your rice is ready, stir in your lentils and half of your onions. Put your pan back on the #hob{} on medium-low heat for a few mins. Test for seasoning and add more salt and pepper to taste. Lastly, stir your spinach through the rice.

Serve your halloumi on top of your rice, spinach and lentil mixture. Top with your leftover cherry tomatoes, remaining onions and a sprinkle of pistachios.

> Great food is all about dimensions. For some people, food has only one dimension: they eat it for fuel. For others it has two dimensions: it not only keeps them going, but it tastes good too. However, as with Oscar winning blockbusters about blue people from Pandora, the full experience can really only be enjoyed in 3D. For this dish, we've added texture in the form of crispy onions and the hearty mouth filling indulgence that is grilled halloumi. Blue and red disposable glasses optional.